foursquare.py - v0.1

A simple python wrapper for the foursquare API.

http://www.foursquare.com
http://api.foursquare.com

Created by Ismail Dhorat @ http://zyelabs.net
Please note: This is a work in progress and does not implement all the API calls just yet.

Usage:
	f = foursquare()
	test = f.test()
	cities = f.get_cities()
	venues = f.get_venues(lat, lon)
	tips = f.get_tips(lat, lon)


Foursquare Methods defined:

get_cities(self)
    Get a list of cities
    
    Args: None
    
    Returns: Dictionary/JSON of All cities

get_tips(self, lat, lon, limit='')
    Get Tips closeby for a given longitude and latitude
    
    args: 
    latitude -- Required
    longitude -- Required
    
    keyword arguments:
    limit -- Limit the number of records returned
    
    Returns: Dictionary/JSON of tips for lat,lon passed

get_venues(self, lat, lon, search='', limit='')
    Get venues close by for a given longitude and latitude
    
    args: 
    latitude -- Required
    longitude -- Required
    
    keyword arguments:
    limit -- Limit the number of records returned
    search -- search for a specific keyword
    
    Returns: Dictionary/JSON of Venues close to Lat, Lon passed

test(self)
    Test if an API request will succeed
    
    Args: None
    
    Returns: 
    True -- Test was successful or
    False -- The query resulted in an Error
